data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
In the XOY rectangular coordinate system, rectangles are drawn that simulate areas of land planted with crops of the same species. The sides of the sections are parallel to the coordinate axes and integer coordinates are at the vertices of the rectangles. Parcels can have common points only on the sides. Each type of culture delivered certain color with the code Cp. (see fig. 1 and fig. 2)
Detailed information about the rectangles in question is recorded in the Teren.in text file, which contains in the first line the positive integer n, which is the number of rectangles. Each of the following n lines of this file contains 5 integers separated by a single space: X1, Y1, X2, Y2, CP.
(X1, Y1) and (X2, Y2) are the coordinates of two opposite vertices of the rectangles, and Cp c ontains the color code of the rectangle.
